          "body": "John turns inward — but not to introspection as the final court. *By this we will know that we are of the truth* — the *this* is the concrete love just commanded — *and will assure our heart before Him in whatever our heart condemns us; for God is greater than our heart and knows all things*. This is one of the New Testament's most pastorally important sentences. The believer's conscience can over-condemn (and the schismatics' propaganda surely amplified that), but God's omniscient knowledge of the believer's real love-in-deed is a higher court than the accusing heart. When the heart does not condemn — when concrete love is actually present — *we have confidence* (*parresia*) before God, and prayer flows freely from a relationship in which obedience and asking are integrated."
